Key Learnings from this Topic (Vehicle Fuel Analytics Dashboard):
Data helps in better decision-making — Raw data becomes useful when converted into insights.
Cost analysis matters — Comparing cost per km shows the real expense of different fuel types.
Sustainability can be measured — CO₂ analysis helps understand environmental impact.
Visualization improves understanding — Charts and dashboards make complex data easier to read.
Vehicle age affects performance — Maintenance and running costs change over time.
Trade-offs are important — Lower fuel prices don’t always mean lower total running costs (like the E85 comparison).
Analytics combines business + technology — Good analysis connects numbers with real-world decisions.
Main takeaway:
Data is most powerful when it turns information into clear actions and smarter choices.
